Photo by @amivitale. Villagers from Nyarusizi, Rwanda prepare to go home after working. The village is located in the mountains near Volcanoes National Park, next to Bisate Lodge, a lush retreat for gorilla trekkers. Nature conservation has been a priority for Rwanda, and the country has had particularly impressive success safeguarding mountain gorillas. Tourism is an important and fast growing sector of the Rwandan economy. Their national parks and wildlife are a significant part of the country's draw and a well cared for asset for tomorrow's generation of Rwandans.

Last week, Rwanda began a 100 day mourning period in honor of the 25th anniversary of the country's genocide. Since the genocide, Rwandans have worked steadily to heal and renew themselves and their country in the years after the genocide, sewing seeds of hope for the future along the way.

